==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aculeate
<hw>A*cu"le*ate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aculeatus</ets>, fr. <ets>aculeus</ets>, dim. of <ets>acus</ets>
needle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a sting;
covered with prickles; sharp like a prickle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having prickles, or sharp points;
beset with prickles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Severe or stinging; incisive.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aculeated</ent>⟦br⟧
